    <text>
        <body>
            <head>317. National Security Decision Directive 310<note n="1" place="foot"
                    type="source" xml:id="d317fn1">Source: <orgName corresp="recft7WGb7Fww0wma"
                        >National Security Council</orgName>, National Security Council
                    Institutional Files, Box SR 097, NSDD 310 [<gloss target="#t_NST_1">
                        <rs type="event" corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">NST</rs>
                    </gloss> Negotiations Round X]. Secret. Negroponte distributed the decision
                    directive to <persName corresp="recjlYSNpDHCqlk6w">Bush</persName>, <persName
                        corresp="rece7NCQ7Hh9DICyN">Shultz</persName>, <persName
                        corresp="rech6OQ6N5EdBVhDo">Carlucci</persName>, <persName
                        corresp="rechGoaAX1JsqtFFE">Herrington</persName>, <persName
                        corresp="recBKslEENmwouTDw">Webster</persName>, <persName
                        corresp="recusSiT3UbixAWkn">Crowe</persName>, and <persName
                        corresp="recqE8tZSa55Z2YwW">Burns</persName> under cover of a July 18
                    memorandum that reads in part: “Agency proposals to limit the scope of technical
                    data exchanged, to specify treaty duration and to define space launch vehicles
                    were deleted from the instructions without prejudice and will be reconsidered as
                    part of the <gloss target="#t_START_1">
                        <rs type="event" corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O">START</rs>
                    </gloss> work program.” (Ibid.)</note>
            </head>
            <opener>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1988-07-18"
                        >July 18, 1988</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p rendition="simple_centre">
                <hi rendition="simple_italic">INSTRUCTIONS FOR THE TENTH <gloss target="#t_NST_1">
                        <rs type="event" corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">NST</rs>
                    </gloss> NEGOTIATING ROUND</hi> (C)</p>
            <p>The attached instructions provide guidance for the tenth round of the <rs
                    type="event" corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">Nuclear and Space Talks</rs> (<gloss
                    target="#t_NST_1">
                    <rs type="event" corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">NST</rs>
                </gloss>), which begins on July 12, 1988, in Geneva. They include the agreements
                reached during my June 1988 meeting with General Secretary <persName
                    corresp="recXTrNyt2vU9QpAl">Gorbachev</persName> in Moscow. (S)</p>
            <closer>
                <signed>
                    <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">
                        <hi rendition="simple_bold">Ronald Reagan</hi>
                    </persName>
                </signed>
            </closer>
            <pb facs="1487" n="1460" xml:id="pg_1460"/>
            <frus:attachment xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
                <note>
                    <hi rendition="simple_bold">Attachment</hi>
                </note>
                <head>
                    <hi rendition="simple_bold">Draft Telegram</hi>
                    <note n="2" place="foot" xml:id="d317fn2">Secret. The Department transmitted the
                        overall instructions to the <orgName corresp="rechbJf4QHaXNGzWb"
                            >Delegation</orgName> to the <rs type="event"
                            corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">Nuclear and Space Talks</rs> in telegram
                        22382, July 12. (Department of State, Central Foreign Policy File,
                        D880591-0430)</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-editorial-annotation"
                            calendar="gregorian" when="1988-07-12">undated</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Subject: Overall instructions for Round X of the U.S.-Soviet Nuclear and Space
                        <rs type="event" corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">Arms Talks</rs> (U)</p>
                <p>Ref: (A) Round X <gloss target="#t_START_1">
                        <rs type="event" corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O">START</rs>
                    </gloss> Instructions<note n="3" place="foot" xml:id="d317fn3">Attached but not
                        printed. The Department transmitted Round X <gloss target="#t_START_1">
                            <rs type="event" corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O">START</rs>
                        </gloss> Instructions to the <orgName corresp="rechbJf4QHaXNGzWb"
                            >Delegation</orgName> to the <rs type="event"
                            corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">Nuclear and Space Talks</rs> in telegram
                        222516, July 12. (Department of State, Central Foreign Policy File,
                        P880088-1905)</note>
                </p>
                <p>(B) Round X <gloss target="#t_DST_1">
                        <rs type="event" corresp="rec0rc9kDG6TIF88N">DST</rs>
                    </gloss> Instructions<note n="4" place="foot" xml:id="d317fn4">Attached but not
                        printed. The Department transmitted Round X <gloss target="#t_DST_1">
                            <rs type="event" corresp="rec0rc9kDG6TIF88N">DST</rs>
                        </gloss> Instructions to the <orgName corresp="rechbJf4QHaXNGzWb"
                            >Delegation</orgName> to the <rs type="event"
                            corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">Nuclear and Space Talks</rs> in telegram
                        222515, July 12. (Department of State, Central Foreign Policy File,
                        N/A)</note>
                </p>
                <p>1. Secret—entire text.</p>
                <p>2. The following is overall guidance for the U.S. <gloss target="#t_NST_1">
                        <rs type="event" corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">NST</rs>
                    </gloss>
                    <orgName corresp="rechbJf4QHaXNGzWb">delegation</orgName> for Round X, which
                    begins on July 12, 1988. Guidance from previous rounds remains in effect except
                    as modified below. Specific guidance for the <gloss target="#t_START_1">
                        <rs type="event" corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O">START</rs>
                    </gloss> and the <rs type="event" corresp="rec0rc9kDG6TIF88N">Defense and
                        Space</rs> Negotiating Groups is provided in reftels.</p>
                <p>3. Principal objectives for Round X include:</p>
                <p>—To build on the progress achieved during the May 29–June 1, 1988 summit in <rs
                        type="event" corresp="recHp9uQv5w7SafI2">Moscow</rs>.</p>
                <p>—To conclude by the earliest possible date the <rs type="agreement-or-mandate"
                        corresp="recHvtjt4uCqCi2Qk">Treaty</rs> on Reduction and Limitation of
                    Strategic Offensive Arms consistent with U.S. principles that we seek only
                    effectively verifiable and stabilizing <rs type="topic"
                        corresp="recHoFOsQcM4e5M4k">reductions</rs>.</p>
                <p>—To prepare the <rs type="topic" corresp="recFsxBGIzqGviY7Z">joint draft
                        text</rs> of a separate agreement concerning the <gloss target="#t_ABM_1"
                        >ABM</gloss>
                    <rs type="agreement-or-mandate" corresp="recKv8RyteDQ8sLn9">Treaty</rs> building
                    on the language of the <rs type="agreement-or-mandate"
                        corresp="recPOnzDG0FI16H1Y">Washington summit joint statement</rs> dated
                    December 10, 1987 and to continue work on its associated protocol.</p>
                <p>—To continue to resist Soviet attempts to produce a key provisions or framework
                    agreement for either <gloss target="#t_START_1">
                        <rs type="event" corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O">START</rs>
                    </gloss> or <gloss target="#t_DST_1">
                        <rs type="event" corresp="rec0rc9kDG6TIF88N">DST</rs>
                    </gloss>.</p>
                <p>—To continue to counter Soviet efforts to hold <gloss target="#t_START_1">
                        <rs type="event" corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O">START</rs>
                    </gloss> negotiations hostage to progress in <rs type="event"
                        corresp="rec0rc9kDG6TIF88N">Defense and Space</rs>.</p>
                <p>—To reaffirm our longstanding concern with Soviet failure to comply with and to
                    correct Soviet violations of the <gloss target="#t_ABM_1">ABM</gloss>
                    <rs type="agreement-or-mandate" corresp="recKv8RyteDQ8sLn9">Treaty</rs>.</p>
                <pb facs="1488" n="1461" xml:id="pg_1461"/>
                <p>—To make it clear that we will not conclude any <rs type="topic"
                        corresp="recAynYh8uzxYGQRH">strategic ARMS</rs> agreements, either in <gloss
                        target="#t_START_1">
                        <rs type="event" corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O">START</rs>
                    </gloss> or <rs type="event" corresp="rec0rc9kDG6TIF88N">Defense and Space</rs>,
                    while the issue of the illegal Soviet <placeName corresp="recZn2IYQQXg4H5Gm"
                        >Krasnoyarsk radar</placeName> remains unresolved, and that we consider the
                    only appropriate resolution to be dismantlement of the radar.</p>
            </frus:attachment>
        </body>
